Description: Implements functional quantile regression for longitudinal 
    functional data using generalized additive models. The package provides 
    tools for fitting quantile regression models with functional covariates, 
    including block bootstrap and wild bootstrap methods for inference and 
    bias adjustment. The methodology accounts for within-cluster dependence 
    through subject-specific random intercepts. Block bootstrap resamples 
    complete subject trajectories to estimate standard errors, while wild 
    bootstrap combines resampling of random effects with residual perturbation 
    for bias adjustment. Methods are described in Battagliola et al. (2024) 
    <doi:10.1007/s13253-024-00601-5> "Quantile regression for longitudinal 
    functional data with application to feed intake of lactating sows" 
    (Journal of Agricultural, Biological, and Environmental Statistics) 
    and Battagliola et al. (2022) <doi:10.1016/j.ecosta.2021.07.003> 
    "A bias-adjusted estimator in quantile regression for clustered data" 
    (Econometrics and Statistics).
